Definition: optical telescope consisting of a large concave mirror that produces an image that is magnified by the eyepiece
Example: Isaac Newton invented the reflecting telescope in 1668
Synonyms: reflector, optical_telescope, optical, telescope, consisting, of, a, large, concave, mirror, that, produces, an, image, is, magnified, by, the, eyepiece, Isaac, Newton, invented, reflecting, in
Category: noun.artifact
